metadata.name: MANOTSAR
metadata.description:
Rasputin, the infamous Russian mystic and advisor to the Romanovs, is often depicted as a dark and mysterious figure in popular culture. His reputed abilities to heal, his reputed influence over the royal family, and his eventual assassination have all contributed to the mystique surrounding him.

The dark and mysterious persona of Rasputin, with his long hair, beard, and flowing robes, would fit perfectly into the visual aesthetic of a Heavy Metal band. His reputation as a controversial and enigmatic figure would also lend a sense of intrigue and mystery to the band's overall image.
